# Task Execution Template

## Purpose

This document turns recurring execution rules into a standard checklist.

## Before Starting

1. clarify whether the task is project-specific work or governance work
2. identify affected documents and repository areas
3. define the expected documentation outputs

## During Execution

1. inspect the current documentation state before changing it
2. note missing links, unclear ownership, and gaps in terminology
3. separate task-local findings from reusable governance conclusions

## Before Commit

### A. Documentation Completeness

- required documents updated
- document links still valid
- new rules placed in shared documents when appropriate

### B. Workflow Completeness

- commit belongs to a single Jira/workstream
- governance work is not mixed with unrelated task work
- summary of changed docs is clear

## Final Report Shape

1. what changed
2. what docs changed
3. what remains open
4. which Jira this belongs to
